<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<strong>IDENTIFIER:</strong> Dr. Dagon, PhD. MSc. BSc</p>
<p><strong>CURRENT FOUNDATION ROLE:</strong> Dr. Dagon has led a long career at the Foundation as a lead researcher in the Department of Sciences. His interdisciplinary, multidisciplinary, and transdisciplinary expertise have made him invaluable in his work for the <a href="/project-ruby">AIAD</a> and <a href="/scp-5366">Department of Sciences</a>.</p>
<p><strong>EXPERTISE:</strong> Dr. Dagon is considered to be a polymath of standard and anomalous research methodologies. His expertise is in determination of properties and effects of sentient anomalies through his background in qualitative data collection methods and of anomalous objects through his background in analytical science techniques. He is often the first to interact with an anomaly upon its arrival to the Department of Sciences to determine which methods would be most effective at determining special containment procedures.<br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
</div>
