<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<strong>IDENTIFIER:</strong> Brian [REDACTED], MA (Current), BEd., BSc.</p>
<p><strong>CURRENT FOUNDATION ROLE:</strong> I am a Canadian graduate student in the field of Science Education. My current research is on how non-science majors develop science literacy skills and a science identity by taking science breadth courses. I am currently applying for PhD programs to look at how the SCP Wiki acts as an informal learning environment for academic literacy skills and how it increases engagement with scientific writing skills. I also have a BSc. where I concentrated on chemistry, biology, and computer science and a BEd. where I specialized in teaching science to elementary students. I am always looking to read and critique things on any of these disciplines or to talk about how to make qualitative research and interviews more realistic! In my off time, I enjoy doing critique on discord and designing games for teaching chemistry to high school and undergraduate students.</p>
<p><strong>HISTORY WITH THE FOUNDATION:</strong> I have been reading the wiki since 2008 when the <a href="/scp-173">SCP-173</a> 4chan post was left printed in a school printer and I had to know more. I only became involved in the community in 2019 because I finally had <a href="/scp-5367">something to write an article about</a>.</p>
